From: Sama Engine <engine@local>
Subject: [PATCH] renderer_vk: track requested resolution separately from clamped-actual

Context — the second trigger
----------------------------
With `bgfx_android_vk_suboptimal_no_recreate.patch` in, the SUBOPTIMAL
rebuild loop is closed.  But on Pixel 9 / Android 16 the team still
saw 648 `Create swapchain` lines over 12 s (was ~600 before, so we're
right back where we started).  `bgfx::frameMs` 12-19 ms, `waitRender`
similar.

The cause is a second self-sustaining rebuild loop, independent of
SUBOPTIMAL:

1. sama calls `bgfx::reset(2424, 1080)` once — `_resolution.width = 2424`
   (the activity's `ANativeWindow_getWidth()`).
2. `RendererContextVK::updateResolution` enters the if-block (initial
   creation), assigns `m_resolution = _resolution` (= 2424×1080).
3. `m_backBuffer.update(...)` creates the swapchain.  The Vulkan driver
   clamps to 2251×1080 (the display-cutout-safe extent) because
   `surfaceCapabilities.maxImageExtent.width` reports 2251.
4. Per the existing comment at `renderer_vk.cpp:3025`, the renderer
   overwrites `m_resolution.width/height` with `m_backBuffer.m_width/m_height`
   so the rest of bgfx sees the *actual* swapchain extent.  After this,
   `m_resolution.width = 2251`.
5. Next frame, `updateResolution()` runs again with `_resolution.width
   = 2424` (sama hasn't called reset again; this is just the
   per-frame resolution propagation).  The comparison at lines 3003-3004
   sees `m_resolution.width (2251) != _resolution.width (2424)` →
   triggers recreate.
6. Recreate clamps to 2251 again → `m_resolution.width = 2251` → loop.

Self-sustaining; the swapchain is rebuilt every single frame for the
entire activity lifetime.  Same cost as the SUBOPTIMAL loop:
`vkDeviceWaitIdle` + `vkDestroySwapchainKHR` + `vkCreateSwapchainKHR`
+ image-view recreation ≈ 15 ms per frame.

Why the existing code overwrites m_resolution
---------------------------------------------
The comment at line 3025 explains it: downstream bgfx code reads
`m_resolution.width/height` for viewport sizing, render-target dims,
etc.  Those need the *actual* (clamped) value, not what was requested.
Overwriting at line 3027 is correct for that purpose.

The bug is using the same field for two purposes: "what should the
rest of bgfx see" (correct: clamped) and "did the application ask for
something new" (incorrect: should compare against last-requested, not
clamped-actual).

The fix
-------
Track the un-clamped requested resolution separately from
`m_resolution.width/height`.  Comparison in `updateResolution` uses
the last-requested values; rest of bgfx still reads
`m_resolution.width/height` and gets the clamped actual.

Three small changes to `RendererContextVK`:

  1. Add `m_lastRequestedWidth / m_lastRequestedHeight` to the struct
     (init'd to 0 — first updateResolution() call will set them).
  2. Prime them at init time (right after `m_resolution = _init.resolution`).
  3. In `updateResolution`:
     - Compare `m_lastRequestedWidth/Height` instead of
       `m_resolution.width/height`.
     - Inside the recreate block, store the *requested* values
       (`_resolution.width/.height`) into the shadow BEFORE the
       backbuffer-clamping line.

Effect: the next-frame comparison sees `m_lastRequestedWidth (2424) ==
_resolution.width (2424)` → no recreate → swapchain alive.  Clamped
`m_resolution.width (2251)` is still what every viewport, scissor, and
render-target sizing path in bgfx reads.  Render output is the same;
we just stop discarding it every frame.

Why option 1 (this patch) over option 2 (engine workaround)
-----------------------------------------------------------
The team flagged a sama-side alternative: read `bgfx::getStats()->width`
after `reset()` and feed that back into the engine's framebuffer-dims
check.  Works, but couples our engine to bgfx's internal clamping
behaviour — fragile across bgfx version bumps, and any other game on
a cutout device hits the same bug.  This patch fixes the root cause
inside bgfx and is upstream-PR-able alongside `bgfx_android_mailbox_present.patch`
and `bgfx_android_vk_suboptimal_no_recreate.patch`.  Three small VK-renderer
patches together describe one coherent "make bgfx behave on modern
Android" change.

Expected impact
---------------
`Create swapchain` count over the activity lifetime drops from ~650 to
1.  `bgfx::frameMs` from ~16 ms to ~0.1 ms.  Per-call timing
(`bgfx_android_vk_call_timing.patch`) should now show all four VK
calls in sub-ms territory.  FPS reaches panel rate.

No visible artefact: the swapchain extent is the same as it has been
all along (2251×1080, the cutout-safe area); we just stop tearing it
down every frame.

Counterpart on engine side: see `docs/NOTES.md` "Follow-up (2026-06-18,
second trigger — clamped-vs-requested resolution rebuild loop)".
---
 bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp | 21 ++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp b/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp
--- a/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp
+++ b/bgfx/src/renderer_vk.cpp
@@ -2085,6 +2085,11 @@
 			{
 				m_resolution = _init.resolution;
 				m_resolution.reset &= ~BGFX_RESET_INTERNAL_FORCE;
+				// Sama: prime the requested-resolution shadow so the
+				// first updateResolution() with the same dimensions
+				// doesn't false-positive a recreate.
+				m_lastRequestedWidth  = _init.resolution.width;
+				m_lastRequestedHeight = _init.resolution.height;

 				m_numWindows = 0;

@@ -3000,8 +3005,8 @@
 			if (false
 			||  m_resolution.formatColor        != _resolution.formatColor
 			||  m_resolution.formatDepthStencil != _resolution.formatDepthStencil
-			||  m_resolution.width              != _resolution.width
-			||  m_resolution.height             != _resolution.height
+			||  m_lastRequestedWidth            != _resolution.width
+			||  m_lastRequestedHeight           != _resolution.height
 			||  m_resolution.reset              != flags
 			||  m_backBuffer.m_swapChain.m_needToRecreateSurface
 			||  m_backBuffer.m_swapChain.m_needToRecreateSwapchain)
@@ -3015,6 +3020,12 @@

 				m_resolution = _resolution;
 				m_resolution.reset = flags;
+				// Sama: remember the un-clamped request so next-frame
+				// updateResolution() compares request-vs-request, not
+				// clamped-actual-vs-request (which loops forever on
+				// cutout devices where the driver permanently clamps).
+				m_lastRequestedWidth  = _resolution.width;
+				m_lastRequestedHeight = _resolution.height;

 				m_textVideoMem.resize(false, _resolution.width, _resolution.height);
 				m_textVideoMem.clear();
@@ -4793,6 +4804,14 @@
 		StateCacheLru<VkImageView, 1024> m_imageViewCache;

 		Resolution m_resolution;
+		// Sama: track last *requested* (un-clamped) resolution separately
+		// from m_resolution.width/height (which is overwritten with the
+		// driver-clamped actual swapchain extent below).  Without this,
+		// next-frame updateResolution() compares clamped-actual against
+		// new-requested and triggers a rebuild loop on cutout devices.
+		// See patches/bgfx_android_vk_clamped_resolution_no_recreate.patch.
+		uint32_t m_lastRequestedWidth  = 0;
+		uint32_t m_lastRequestedHeight = 0;
 		float m_maxAnisotropy;
 		bool m_depthClamp;
 		bool m_wireframe;
